content.detailedDescription: I was driving home from work down the 80 toward oakland out of berkeley . around 2am. i looked toward berkeley hills because i've seen curious lights around that time once before, to this day i always look toward them as i drive. earlier in that week i had seen something odd, odd enough to ask my boss' opinion as well as text my mother and next eldest brother. this time however was undeniable. the curiosity of anyone having shared this encounter or the overall questioning my own two eyes kept me searching for explanantion. and months later here i am sharing the story at the only place i know it will not be automatically dismissed. i saw a green ball, white in the center like a burning aura come straight down into our atmosphere, stop momentarily, then leave in the exact path it came. the look of it was unsettling, how nimble it was and the speed at which it moved also. i saw a cop later that morning maybe 8 hours later while i gassed up and asked how or if i should report this. maybe it's a threat to security for all i know. he shrugged it off and stated "yeah, we get this once in awhile". months later i think of it often enough to google "how to report a ufo sighting" and take the time to write this. i assure you "the green fireball" is absolutely something that exists. i am not a "storyteller" nor do have a reason to write this other than to share it with ...Someone. cop stated there were no other reports sadly. i will say lawrence livermore labs test site is relatively close, and after 3 strange things i've seen total in 2 years living here , i can only chalk it up to having to do with them. this is the nearest thing i have to an explanation. i will say.. to anyone listening, that there a lot of strange things happening in this bay area over the last year. if you were to spend your focus anywhere "in hopes of seeing something", this place has more than enough should you have the patience. i count myself lucky in an innocent game of roulette , looking over at the right times after slightly being on the lookout since the 1st strange light i saw. hope this helps or gives somebody else peace of mind that mightve seen the same thing as it fell on deaf ears like it did for me.
content.summary: I looked to berkeley hills driving home. green ball/white center enters atmosphere over hills, stops, leaves straight upward

content.detailedDescription:

the tall alien had skin that resembled a reptile. very rough like. his eyes weren't big but more thin and long also had a human appearance.. his eyes were dark but had color to them.. no lips and no prominent nose and his presence very ominous/dark.


the little ones where kind of like your typical grey explaination but were very playful. they could turn invisible at will and could speak to you "telepathically". they had smooth light grey skin. their eyes were not very big but they were very dark. they kind of resembled 4 year old children

content.detailedDescription:
At 9:40pm on december 31, 2015 four of us were sitting at the dinner table
playing a board game. my husband was looking out the window and he said
"what is that?"  he pointed out what he was looking at and said two of
these identical objects had flown over already.  the lights were on inside
the house and he was sitting closest to the window so the objects were
visible beyond the reflections in the glass at night.
we headed out the patio door to get a better look and in the distance we
saw more of these objects. as they came into view each looked identical.
there were a total of four objects that were observed outside with a
fairly large space in between, all objects were flying in single file.
during this time i grabbed my cell phone off the table we were sitting at
and started recording.  the objects made no sound as approaching or
departing our field of view. each object emitted a white flickering light.
as the last of the objects was coming into view we all ran inside through
to the front of the house to see what they were doing on the other side;
all the while recording. the objects appeared to fan out in the distance
and disappear from view. we approximate that the altitude of the objects
is around 500 feet up and they may have been automobile sized objects but
was hard to discern as only light from the object was observed.
there were no vehicle traffic sounds drowning out any sound that may have
been coming from the objects. there was a dog barking in the distance and
when at the front of the house there is the sound of an inflatable
christmas display on the porch.
content.summary: 4 witnesses observed 6 glowing orbs traveling in a straight line.

content.detailedDescription:
As a mufon investigator, i was investigating a case (73544) and finishing the paperwork. i had just shown my wife and sister-in-law the video in that file.  they were going out to pick up dinner at about 2100 (9pm) when my wife came back into the house urgently telling me to come outside. "there is one of them in the sky now" she said.  i grabbed my ipad and ran out to see what she was talking about.  i looked up in the western sky (268deg) to see this yellowish red-orange light floating along with the breeze.  immediately capturing the object with my theodolite, thereby giving me all of the data on its position and travel (listed in the report).  the image is so poor it is not worth inserting.

the glowing light drifted southward for about another minute before fading gently out. i believe this could be similar to what was sighted in case 
(73544). as i have observed many things in my 32 year military career, i can say confidently this was a "chinese lantern".  my belief is since the very popular move "frozen" came out; which depicted these in certain scenes, pranksters will insure we will see more.

i am submitting this report more or less for information only.
content.summary: One yellowish red-orange light floating along with the breeze.

content.detailedDescription:
These objects were captured by accident on an i-phone 4-s.  the location was on a ranch north west of canadian, texas at 05:23hrs on october 8th, 2015.  this was the site of a drilling operation where i was working the overnight shift of monitoring telemetry data of the down hole drilling equipment.

towards the end of my shift, i stepped out on to the porch of the office and saw that the moon and venus were rising in the east at approximately 05:23 hours.  i decided to take some pictures of this with the drilling rig in the foreground.  i proceeded to snap away shooting three to four wide shots, then i zoomed in as close as i could to get a closeup of the moon and venus.  i took about three or four pics at that setting.

shortly there after i zoomed out and took three more pictures and then went back inside the office.

after my shift was over i sat down to eat breakfast and began looking at the pictures i shot at the moon rise.

i was startled to see the objects i captured, unknowingly.

it appears to be a flight of four objects appearing from left to right in trail formation and jinking right and left in a "follow the leader" game of chase.

the objects appeared to increase in illumination.  they also change positions in relation to the moon and venus.  i did not see them in my i-phone screen and they were not visible to my eye.  it was after i zoomed in and took the close ups of the moon and venus, then zoomed out, that the objects had passed or at least flown out of frame.
content.summary: While taking pictures of the crescent moon, venus rise against the drilling rig none was observed with the naked eye.  after taking several pictures, over a three to four minute time frame i returned into the sleeping trailer.  i found objects on photos.

content.detailedDescription:
I stepped out on the front porch last night.  sky was fairly clear and many stars were visible.  i was drawn to look up because of a flashing.  i saw what looked like a very high airplane, but could see it was much higher than the planes i'm accustomed to seeing in the area.  i was facing south, and the lights were a bit east of due south.

all in the matter of no more than 4 seconds, i caught a first flash.  then at what would have to be a very fast speed, i saw it flash again at several degrees higher distance than the first flash.  that second light also flashed for only a split second, and again, after the same interval of time, i saw it flash a third time.  if the first flash was 40 degrees above the horizon, the third flash was about 50 degrees.  all of these flashes were in a perfectly straight line.

instead of blinking out like the two flashes, this third appearance of the light remained on at the same split second that it made a hairpin change of direction, shooting off at approximately a 5 degree angle from its original path.  this shooting off was back in the direction it had come, so it was shooting off lower in the sky than from where i saw the first light.  the light was steady from the third flash, on through this streaking off on the hairpin turn.  this exit was brief, it covered a few degrees in the sky and blinked off.

i stayed on the porch, checking myself about what i'd just seen.  i confirmed that it wasn't a plane, since it behaved unlike any seen before in the area.  i considered whether i maybe saw two objects, one flashing three times and going off, then with another object, like a meteor, somehow making this hairpin streak from the exact location of the third light.  that didn't seem at all likely.  it had looked like one, continuous and self-contained, organic event.

i waited for a couple of minutes before going inside again, in case i would catch sight of the light/object again - i saw nothing more, so finally went in and told my wife what i'd seen.

it was all relatively unspectacular, the light(s) being at such a great distance, but the impossibly tight turn, that sudden change of direction obviously makes the behavior of the phenomenon classic.

i do wonder if i'll see a report somewhere of someone else in the area seeing the same thing.  i'd very much like to know.

thanks for reading.  happy to report to mufon - not a breathtaking event, but it was, i do believe, a ufo, so wanted to do my bit and report it.
content.summary: High, flashing light in straight path, sudden hairpin turn

content.detailedDescription: I was out on my driveway at 7:15pm on january 2, 2016. the sky was star lit and clouds were maybe at 25,000 to 30,000 feet. i looked up towards the north. i saw an aircraft flying from the ne going sw. it appeared to be going the speed of a jet plane or a little faster in a strait line. at first i thought is was an airplane, however it did not have the lights that airplanes use. at that point i knew it was a ufo. there was no sound at all. the ufo appeared to be round in front and a flat rear and had a dome with yellowish lights, some seem to pulsate and some weren't. the body of the craft was greyish and was fuzzy on the edges. i only had around 10 to 15 seconds to observe it until it flew out of sight. when i observed the object i did not feel anything. however, i did not sleep well that night, i had nightmares all night ( that does not happen to me ever). while i fill this report out i am getting chills and goose bumps up and down my back. i am a relatively fearless person what happened to me afterwards was strange.

content.detailedDescription: The following event took place at night over disney world. i noticed some red glowing lights that were able to change in number, orientation and even appeared to merge back together. the pattern of lights consisted of 1 to 4 separate but equal sized lights. there were definitely no sounds associated with that of a blimp, plane or helicopter. the lights were able to hover and were obviously under intelligent control. i photographed the light objects with a mediocre h5 sony camera. i believed that all i would see were some blurry lights on the computer monitor. much to my surprise, there was also a clear outline of what appeared to be a craft. the apparent craft also seemed to have a propulsion system. the propulsion system seemed to be emitting a white energy or light. there were other strange objects in the digital image that i could not detect in the field. i can only explain the phenomenon as some sort of electrical disturbance perhaps a little like connected, irregular loops of dancing energy. these energy loops were irregular in shape and appeared in different colors. these energy loops were visible on both sides of the craft and the red light objects. i thought these light loops were the result of camera movement. then i rationalized that if movement had produced the colored loops of energy, then why were they different colors? why did the craft and red colored lights remain in sharp focus?
content.summary: The craft seemed to have a bright white propulsion system along with changing light colors

content.detailedDescription: It was the spring or summer of 1967 or 68 myself and 3 other friends were hanging out in exeter missouri when someone noticed a light moving in the sky. it would move one direction then another then started moving to the south. we got in the car drove about a mile and got out to watch it when 2 jets one from the east the other from the west turned to line up side by side and was behind the light. they followed it for maybe 30 seconds then the light shot across the sky and left the jets like they were just setting there. the jets were low enough that we could tell they were not commercial but all we could tell about the light is that was just a light. i'm 65 years old now and since that time when i look at the sky i think about that night and long to see the light again but have not!
content.summary: Watched 2 jets chase it for about 5 minutes then it shot across the night sky at unbelievable speed! gone!!

content.detailedDescription: It was approximately 9:05pm.  my boyfriend and i were out on our front porch smoking.  we searched the sky for the moon like we normally do but we didnt see it.  i noticed to the west of us was an airplane descending at an unusually steep angle.  my boyfriend then mentioned that he hoped it would crash because he wanted to see something exciting.  i then faced north and found the little dipper.  i moved my eyes northeast and found what i thought was the big dipper.  while staring at the star formation, one of the stars moved fast going east.  we knew it wasnt a plane because of the speed at the altitude and the quick direction change. it disappeared then reappeared and headed northeast again. seconds later it faded away.  we waited approx 5 minutes looking for more movement. shortly after, i noticed a helicopter not far from my house headed west.  i had a weird feeling when the helicopter passed but i couldnt explain it. we immediately downloaded a constellation app on our android phone and discovered the big star the orb disappeared next to was polaris.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Orb with various speeds and direction disappeared by polaris star
